CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 27, 1959, page A3, reads: "Top Worker - Mrs. Virginia Valentine co-chairman of the Tri-Borough area, and NAACP executive board member, proudly shows her Century Club plaque which she recieved for obtaining 100 NAACP memberships during the 1959 campaign. Nine other workers also recieved the Century Club award. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of woman wearing dark dress with three quarter length sleeves, and two brooches on chest, holding plaque inscribed "N.A.A.C.P. Century Club 1959" standing in front of brick wall
